\end_inset

The Kumaraswamy distribution for the given parameters in the title of the
 plot.
 The relatively large 
\emph on
n
\emph default
 given better convergence between the empirical and theoretical curves.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:kum_cdf_small_n"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 shows the CDF of the Kumaraswamy distribution distribution where 
\emph on

\begin_inset Formula $n=100$
\end_inset

.
 
\emph default
As can be noted from the plot, smaller values of 
\emph on
n
\emph default
 can lead to empirical CDF curves differing from the theoretical.
 Increasing the size of 
\emph on
n
\emph default
 leads to better convergence of the empirical and theoretical.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\begin_inset Float figure
wide false
sideways false
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
